Previous games from this company have all been total favourites. This one - I can't be bothered even finishing it. Boring, hints are less than helpful, just not up to the wonderful other games from these people. I have now re-bought The Lost City, to play again, it is so so much better! Frankly, I wouldn't bother with this game. Hoping the developers will raise their game for the next one.

Good game but not worth the money. There was only an hour or so's worth of gameplay - I finished it quickly enough that the store would still allow me a refund when I came here to review. If it was half the price it'd be fine, but there were a few bugs (they disappeared when I refreshed the app, but still) and again the game was quite small (and irritating to navigate, considering the unnecessarily huge map). Plus the hermit dude was very uncanny valley which I didn't enjoy.
Love Fire Maple Games so much.
good game but it was super easy to me. I only had to use a hint 3 times. and was done in 2 days. It would have been one day but my internet went out for half a day.

I love the Fire Maple games, they are quite challenging and the graphics are good, but this one was not on par with the rest of them, the storyline was flawed, some of the things didn't really make sense and it was very short. Hope the next one will be better!
Fantastic game well put together, great graphics and excellent story line! Can't wait for another game, I purchased them all in one week! Thanks for not having DEMONIC or WITCH CRAFT STORY LINES.

I've enjoyed immensely all the Fire Maple games to date. They always offer plenty to get your teeth into. This one was as polished as I've come to expect, but much less of a challenge, and I found myself simply working through from one step to the next in quite a short time. Enjoyable, but disappointing in comparison to its predecessors.

I downloaded the Thickety Creek app the evening of May 25, 2019. When it opens I have only a black screen. if I let it sit, it pauses. Then I click on it to wake it from its pause...still just a black screen. I've played all of Fire Maple games and never had a problem before. Either Fire Maple fixes it for me or I'll need my money back ASAP. I will change the rating if it is fixed.

Beautiful graphics and great storyline, just too many continue pages (38) which detracts from the thrill of the game. You could advance the pictures automatically and/or add a skip to push the game along. This would not detract from the game and adds sophistication.

Fun little game. Some things were not intuitive and I had to cheat and use Help. It would be good if the map's images were larger and/or could be enlarged. I had difficulty deciphering some of them, to find the place I wanted to get to. Finished in one evening. Overall, entertaining, challenging, and worth the $3 price.

I did prefer some of this publisher's older games to this one. However, it was still a great little game and still worth playing. And to all the reviews belly-aching over $3, really? You can hardly buy popcorn at a movie theater for that price, it's not that much.

Another great Maple Creek game. Four stars because, 1) its very short (one sitting, see #4), 2) still no fast travel map (i hate going back and forth), 3) there's a number of times the hint had to be used and having to wait 10 minutes is a real pain in the butt, and 4) for $2.99 it's overpriced. Other games have much more to do, longer gameplay and some even have bonus gameplay. Otherwise, the game is great.
Fun game but not as good as their other games. Would be nice to be able to transport via map. Could definitely be longer also.

I got lost a few times, toing and froing through all the many scenes. The map was hopeless, you should be able to click on the images and be taken to that location otherwise why give us a map at all?! Other than that i enjoyed the game.
It's a great game but it could have been better . I missed the vibrancy of the graphics. Also I missed the puzzles and the diary. For me The Lost City is still the best .

I wanted to love it but was left disappointed. As always Maple fire graphics are fantastic but this game was short and easy compared to the others produced by these developers. The Lost City was so much better. You're gonna have to step it up a bit to compete in the adventure game market. Sorry Maple Fire. :(
Loved this game. Squirrel is a favorite. Looking forward to new games.
good game

Fire Maple make excellent puzzle games and this one comes up to the high standard of the others in the series. Really missed the quick travel between scenes option, but otherwise a great game all round.

I've been playing Fire Maple games for years. A true favorite of mine. They are simple, well made fun. Only issue I've ever had with their games is the speed. It seems very slow getting from one place to the next and this particular game didn't have the usual mini games or challenges that the others have had. But otherwise. üåüüåüüåüüåüüåü

Fire maple games are usually visually stunning, have mood and experience enhancing music, and a story and characters you can become invested in. Thickety Creek has, and is, none of those things. the puzzles are rudimentary and the storyline has been totally phoned in, no effort was made to make the story have depth. The end was an afterthought. My family loves Fire Maple Games and eagerly awaits their next game, however, they have done the unexpected this time and thoroughly disappointed us.
Good game. Great animations but WAY too short for 3 dollars. I'll continue to support your company because I love your games, but way too short.

I'm really happy that Fire Maple Games have released a new game! This game was really good, took a while to figure out everything. Graphics lovely. Bit slow & sluggish on the controls side unfortunately.
Awesome! Instabuy after playing all the other Firemaple games. The music is great in this one.
Another super fun game, graphics are excellent, fun story line, great puzzles, like all of your games, wicked AWESOME, can't wait for the next one.
Terrific Game Just what you've come to expect from Fire Maple Games. Loved it, just like all their other games. puzzles aren't overly hard. Only had a lil issue with one. Can't wait for the next one.

Like many others, I have been eagerly awaiting this game ever since the initial screenshots over two years ago. However, it seems as though the intention was twice the length of the game but it was truncated and pushed out. Still easily worth the money though even though it just took an evening to play through. Can anyone tell me why there are still so few decent adventure games on Android/iPhone after all these years?
